  "original_title": "Sri Lanka warned of floods, rough seas if heavy rains continue",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka warned of floods, rough seas if heavy rains continue",
      "author": "Neshella Perera",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Irrigation Department has issued a flood warning to areas around the Attanagalu, Kalu, Kelani, Ging and Nilwala rivers as the river basins are already saturated with water posing a threat of floods if rain continues.",
        "The Department of Meteorology issued a red notice on the country\u2019s prevailing weather situation on Monday September 05, valid for 24 hours.",
        "Very heavy showers above 150mm may occur in parts of the Western and Sabaragamuwa provinces and Kandy, Nuwara-Eliya, Galle and Matara districts, the notice said.",
        "Hanwella in the Colombo district has reported rainfall of 150.5mm, Waharaka in Kegalle district 133mm and Awissawella 114mm.",
        "A red notice was also issued warning of rough sea and strong winds gusting up to (60-70) kmph along the coast extending from Puttalam to Pottuvil via Colombo, Galle and Hambantota due to active Southwest Monsoon conditions.",
        "There is a possibility of an increase in swell waves (about 2.5 \u2013 3.0 m high). It is advised not to venture out to sea for\u00a0 fishing or naval activities in the aforementioned areas in the next 24 hours, the notice said.",
        "The general public has been advised to be vigilant with regard to weather conditions and take adequate precautions to minimise damages caused by lightning activity. The public is also advised to pay close attention to Met Department notices. (Colombo/Sep05/2022)"
      ],
